    {
      "id": "surface-2-facet-migration-review.flow-agents-workflow.claim-surface-claim-facet-migration-reviewed-26-files-migrated-production-code-kit-adapter-test-and-eval-fixture-bundles-kontourai-surface-bumped-to-2-0-0-schemaversion-literals-bumped-to-5-wherever-flow-agents-constructs-a-bundle-one-deliberate-exception-kits-veritas-governance-adapter-readiness-to-trust-bundle-mjs-stays-on-the-legacy-surface-schemaversion-3-shape-and-is-clearly-labeled-because-its-output-is-validated-by-kontourai-flow-s-vendored-hachure-0-5-1-schema-enum-2-3-4-surface-required-which-has-not-shipped-the-facet-rename-bump-yet-confirmed-by-a-real-test-failure-test-veritas-governance-kit-sh-when-the-migration-was-first-attempted-there-then-reverted-with-an-explanatory-comment-full-ci-baseline-evals-ci-run-baseline-sh-all-3-lanes-37-checks-passes-clean-locally-and-in-ci-pr-277-runtime-and-kit-workflow-contracts-usage-feedback-jobs-node-scripts-ci-trust-reconcile-js-bundle-delivery-trust-bundle-exits-0-with-zero-divergences-against-a-small-fast-representative-reconcilable-claim-set-content-boundary-source-tree-validation-context-map-drift-static-eval-suite-veritas-governance-kit-integration-narrowed-from-an-initial-one-claim-per-manifest-command-design-after-that-heavier-design-tripped-trust-reconcile-s-180s-per-command-ci-timeout-on-the-two-slowest-suites-test-workflow-sidecar-writer-sh-antigaming-suite-sh-which-independently-pass-in-2m6s-1m18s-locally-and-in-the-ci-jobs-that-run-the-full-registry-directly",
      "subjectType": "workflow-critique",
      "subjectId": "surface-2-facet-migration/review",
      "facet": "flow-agents.workflow",
      "claimType": "workflow.critique.review",
      "fieldOrBehavior": "Claim.surface -> Claim.facet migration reviewed: 26 files migrated (production code, kit adapter test, and eval/fixture bundles), @kontourai/surface bumped to ^2.0.0, schemaVersion literals bumped to 5 wherever flow-agents constructs a bundle. One deliberate exception (kits/veritas-governance/adapter/readiness-to-trust-bundle.mjs) stays on the legacy surface/schemaVersion-3 shape and is clearly labeled, because its output is validated by @kontourai/flow's vendored hachure@0.5.1 schema (enum [2,3,4], surface required), which has not shipped the facet-rename bump yet -- confirmed by a real test failure (test_veritas_governance_kit.sh) when the migration was first attempted there, then reverted with an explanatory comment. Full CI baseline (evals/ci/run-baseline.sh, all 3 lanes, 37 checks) passes clean locally and in CI (PR #277 Runtime and Kit / Workflow Contracts / Usage Feedback jobs). node scripts/ci/trust-reconcile.js --bundle delivery/trust.bundle exits 0 with zero divergences against a small, fast, representative reconcilable-claim set (content-boundary, source-tree-validation, context-map-drift, static-eval-suite, veritas-governance-kit-integration) -- narrowed from an initial one-claim-per-manifest-command design after that heavier design tripped trust-reconcile's 180s-per-command CI timeout on the two slowest suites (test_workflow_sidecar_writer.sh, antigaming-suite.sh), which independently pass in 2m6s/1m18s locally and in the CI jobs that run the full registry directly.",
      "value": "pass",
      "createdAt": "2026-07-02T18:23:15Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-07-02T18:23:15Z",
      "impactLevel": "medium",
      "verificationPolicyId": "policy:workflow.critique.review",
      "status": "verified"
    }
